name: Bassnectar
bio: Lorin Ashton, better known under his stage name Bassnectar, is an American DJ and record producer.
label: Amorphous

name: Skrillex
bio: Sonny John Moore, known professionally as Skrillex, is an American electronic dance music producer, DJ, singer, songwriter and multi-instrumentalist.
label: OWSLA

name: The Chainsmokers
bio: The Chainsmokers is an American DJ/producer duo consisting of Andrew Taggart and Alex Pall.The EDM-pop duo achieved a breakthrough with their 2014 song "#Selfie", which was a top twenty single in several countries.
label: Disruptor

name: Jauz
bio: Sam Vogel, better known by his stage name Jauz (pronounced: jaws),is an American DJ and electronic dance music producer based in Los Angeles, United States.
label: Spinnin'

name: Martin Garrix
bio: Martin Garrix is a Dutch music producer and DJ. He began releasing singles in 2012, but became widely known after his single "Animals" was a worldwide hit, reaching the top ten of many charts across Europe in late 2013 and early 2014, and reaching number one in the UK, Belgium and on the Billboard Hot Dance Club Songs chart.
label: Spinnin'

name: Dillon Francis
bio: Dillon Hart Francis (born October 5, 1987) is an American DJ, record producer, comedian, composer and musician.
label: Dim Mak

name: Flux Pavilion
bio: Joshua Steele, better known by his stage name Flux Pavilion, is an English DJ, EDM producer, singer-songwriter and label owner who has been performing since 2008.
label: Never Say Die

name: Rusko
bio: Christopher William Mercer (born 26 January 1985) is a British electronic dubstep producer and DJ.
label: Mad Decent

name: Tipper
bio: David Tipper, or Tipper for short (born c. 1976 Wimbledon, London) is a British composer and producer specializing in electronic music that ranges from ambient, through trip hop, to uptempo nu skool breaks. His live performances consist largely of his own unreleased compositions, and he is noted for scratching his own sounds over his music, creating a live element of turntablism stemming from prowess early in his career as a vinyl DJ.
label: Tippermusic

name: Datsik
bio: Troy Beetles, better known by his stage name Datsik, is a Canadian music producer and DJ. His first release was in the spring of 2009; he has since played at venues all over the world.
label: Firepower Records

name: Marshmello
bio: Marshmello (stylized marshmello) is an electronic dance music producer and DJ. He first gained international recognition by remixing songs by Jack U and Zedd, and later collaborated with artists including Omar LinX, Ookay, Jauz and Slushii. In January 2017, his song "Alone" appeared on the US Billboard Hot 100 chart.
label: Monstercat

name: Tame Impala
bio: Tame Impala is a psychedelic rock project by the Australian musician Kevin Parker.
label: Modular Recordings
singles: Feels Like We Only Go Backwards
The Less I Know The Better

name: Tchami
bio: Martin Bresso, known by his stage name Tchami, is a French producer and DJ from Paris. He is regarded as a pioneer of the Future house genre.
label: Confession

name: Oliver Heldens
bio: Oliver Heldens is a Dutch DJ and electronic music producer from Rotterdam. His 2013 song, "Gecko", caught the attention of fellow Dutch DJ Tiesto, who signed him to his label, Musical Freedom, and released the track with vocals from British singer Becky Hill on June 23, 2014. Heldens also has a weekly podcast titled "Heldeep Radio", which has been ongoing for over 2 years.
label: Future House

name: Tiesto
bio: Tijs Michiel Verwest, born 17 January 1969), better known by his stage name Tiesto, is a Dutch DJ and record producer. He is named "the Greatest DJ of All Time" by MixMag magazine in a poll voted by the fans. In 2013, he was voted by DJ Magazine readers as the "best DJ of the last 20 years".
label: Musical Freedom

name: Truth
bio: Tristan Roake and Andre Fernandez, better known as "Truth", are a production duo from Christchurch, New Zealand. Now based in San Francisco, California, Truth have toured extensively including numerous USA tours, four tours of the UK and Europe and a tour of Latin America.
label: Deep, Dark & Dangerous
